member.name: T:Report.ReportCommand
member.summary: Implements AutoCAD .NET extension commands for Reports.
member.remarks:
Most of the reports are implemented with Interop for Civil3D COM API for now. This is because .NET reports are initially ported from VBA reports. That's why most of the .NET report code is VBA style, but not .NET style. For example, array o string is used to hold the report data rather than a class or struct.
As Civil 3D .NET API becomes mature, new reports should be implemented using .NET API. DO NOT just copy the existed report code.

member.name: T:Report.ReportEntry
member.summary: Report entries for tool box. The shared method names are used as macro name in the tool box editor.
member.remarks: Module ReportEntry holds shared functions for Civil Toolbox. Before Civil 2011, the toolbox can only access shared functions in .NET assembly. We add this to make compatible with legacy toolbox configuration file. This can be removed after we update the configuration file to use command names.
